<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-01-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-01-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="438" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d438">
                        <head>438. Telegram 1353 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d438fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                                611.93/1–1156. Confidential; Priority.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-01-11">January 11, 1956, 2
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d438-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d438-1"/>
                        <p>1353. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Would appreciate prior to tomorrow’s meeting text any public reply that
                            may have been made by then to Peiping Allegation of US overflight
                            Manchuria carried FBIS item 1949 1/10 or any instructions on reply if
                                <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> should raise
                            subject.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1"><hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>